<dl id="n35012d"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n35" href="#n35012d">N35 (VI.B.24)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n35all.htm#n35012d"> 12(d)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> tantony pig</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">Anthony or Tantony Pig. The favourite or smallest pig in the litter. &mdash; to follow like a tantony pig, i;e; St Anthony&apos;s pig; to follow close at one&apos;s heels. <small> Captain Francis Grose, <a name="FGCD" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#FGCD"><cite title="source">A Classical Dictionary of the Vulgar Tongue</cite></a> (1785) ANT-APR</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
